Self-styled ‘wahala musician’ Habeeb Okikiola aka Portable has paid a visit to his ‘mothers’ in the Sango area of Lagos State. The singer, who recently got N50million brand ambassadorial deal with billionaire businessman, Obi Cubana and was also reported to have crashed his new Range Rover which he blamed his ‘enemies’ for being responsible visited his ‘mothers’ for spiritual intervention. The viral video which showed the “Zazu” crooner’s crashed car saw him also claim the accident was a spiritual attack for which he needs to seek prayers from his ‘mothers.’   Abacha didn’t loot but kept fund away from thieving…     No one should be imprisoned for weed – Naira Marley     Ex-BBNaija’s Jay Paul joins Tinsel series cast   In a series of videos posted on his Instagram page, Portable who visited some elderly women who he claimed were his mothers’, credited their accounts with undisclosed sums as they cheered and congratulated him on his ambassadorial deal with the herbal drink. While celebrating his success, one of the ‘mothers’ placed her hand on the singer’s back as she prayed for its sustenance and rebuked the plans of the wicked against the fast-rising singer with him on his knees and others around claiming the prayers. Portable captioned the post: “ZAzuu Mothers.”